               <t:note>
               
                  <t:ab type="history">Dabra Dāmmo is the name of a flat-topped mountain, or amba, in <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5932Tegray">Bǝḥerāwi Kǝllǝlāwi Mangǝśti Tǝgrāy</t:placeName> . 
                  This mountain is a steeply rising plateau of trapezoidal shape, about 1000 by 400 m in dimension.
                  It is north west of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC1212Addigr">ʿAddigrat</t:placeName>, in the  central part of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC5932Tegray">Bǝḥerāwi Kǝllǝlāwi Mangǝśti Tǝgrāy</t:placeName>
                     region, close to the border with
                     <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/LOC2991Eritre">Eritrea</t:placeName>. It is the site of the monastery of <t:placeName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/INS0105DD">Dabra Dāmmo ʾAbuna ʾAragāwi</t:placeName>.
                  
                  </t:ab>
               
               </t:note>
            
